Police detained a shooter in the Los Angeles airport
Police detained a shooting suspect in the Los Angeles airport.
Previously it became known that in one of the airport terminals shots were fired from a rifle.
Police and rescue services evacuated people from the building.
The perpetrator was wounded in a shootout with police, there is no information about his identity.
Police are searching for his possible accomplices.
Presumably, several people were injured during the shootout.
It is noted that Barack Obama has been informed of the incident.
